Cell.Data: Civil War Begins, Fort Sumter attacked by Confederate Forces. Union Surrenders Fort Sumter after 2 days of bombardment.
Confederate ironclad USS Merrimack and Union ironclad USS Monitor reach a draw in Chesapeake Bay. Is considered a turning point in Naval warfare from wooden ships to steel.
Higher casualty rate then all other American wars combined. Union victory.
Robert E. Lee's forces attacked by George McClellan's Union army. Union army suffers heavy casualties over 7 days of fighting and retreats. Confederate Victory.
General Stonewall Jackson leads the Confederate army to Victory. Union forces devastated and Union Major General John Pope is discharged after being blamed for loss.
Bloodiest single day battle in American History. Battle is tactically a draw, but Union forces managed to stop Robert E. Lee's Maryland Campaign.
Union forces routed by the entrenched Confederate forces. Multiple frontal assaults resulted in heavy losses for Union troops. Confederate Victory.
Robert E. Lee's "perfect" battle. In the face of overwhelming Union forces doubling the size of his army he tactically won the battle. Confederate Victory.
29,495 Confederate forces Captured. With the capture of Vicksburg the Union now completely controls the Mississippi River.
Confederate Victory. Most significant Union defeat in the Western Theater.

On May 4th Ulysses S. Grant led 120,000 Union forces into Virginia, attempting to end the War. A day later they confronted the Confederate Army in what became known as the Battle of the Wilderness. Fighting in dense woodlands, some men were burned alive by forest fires. The battle was Indesisive, but the Union forces continued their offensive in the Virginia Overland Campaign.
Confederate Victory. Ulysses S. Grant makes tactical errors that result in the loss of thousands of troops. One of the last Battles in the Overland Campaign.
Union Victory. Sherman captures and burns Atlanta, quickening the end of the war.
Savannah Campaign (Sherman's March to the Sea)
Savannah Campaign (Sherman's March to the Sea)
After Sherman's victory at Atlanta he begins the Savannah Campaign with his Union forces.
Union Victory. One of the largest Union victories of the Civil War.
Sherman and the Union army captures Savannah. He offers it to President Lincoln as a Christmas Present
Union Victory. Lots of trench warfare with over 30 miles of trench lines. Lee retreats.
From December 20 to February 1, South Carolina, Mississippi, Florida, Alabama, Georgia, Louisiana, and Texas Secede.
Lincoln takes office of the President of the United States of America and delivers his inaugural address.
From April 17 to May 20, Virginia, Arkansas, Tennessee and North Carolina Secede.
Lincoln Addresses Congress to Enlist Union army

Commands Confederate Army of Northern Virginia.
Lincoln issues an executive order that frees all slaves. This makes abolition a central point of the Civil War.
Jackson dies from injuries sustained at Chancellorsville. (Was hit by friendly fire)
Ulysses S. Grant Appointed Commander of the Union Armies
At the Appomattox Court House Robert E. Lee surrenders to Ulysses S. Grant, effectively ending the Civil War.

Lincoln succumbs to the wounds from the Assassination
